<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She returned to her broadcasting duties last week after a sun-soaked summer holiday to Turkey. </p>

<p>And Ashley Roberts exuded autumnal chic as she left the Global Radio studios on Wednesday afternoon after recording her Heart FM show. </p>

<p>The former Pussycat Dolls singer, 38, looked stylish in a vibrant floral midi-dress and bright blue stilettos as she strutted through central London.</p>

<p>Fashionista: Ashley Roberts exuded autumnal chic as she left the Global Radio studios on Wednesday afternoon after recording her Heart FM show</p>

<p>The radio presenter perfectly matched her sky blue heels with a silver chained mini bag that draped over her shoulder. </p>

<p>The blonde beauty styled her voluminous tresses in an effortless straight 'do and opted for natural make-up. </p>

<p>Ashley wore a pair of round gold rimmed shades to protect her eyes from the September sun. </p>

<p>Flower power: The former Pussycat Dolls singer, 38, looked stylish in a vibrant floral midi-dress and bright blue stilettos as she strutted through central London </p>

<p>Blue-tiful: The radio presenter perfectly matched her sky blue heels with a silver chained mini bag that draped over her shoulder </p>

<p>Plenty to smile about: The blonde beauty styled her voluminous tresses in an effortless straight 'do and opted for natural make-up</p>

<p>Ashley revealed last month she is open to the idea of adopting a child in the future.</p>

<p>Speaking in an interview with Fabulous magazine, she said: 'I'm definitely open to the idea of adoption.</p>

<p> 'You just never know what the future is going to bring and the most important thing is to be happy and, whether my body naturally has kids or not, we'll see what life brings. I'm definitely open to that.'</p>

<p>Ashley also reflected on dating following her split from Italian Strictly Come Dancing professional Giovanni Pernice, 29. </p>

<p>The couple called time on their year-long romance in January after meeting during Ashley's stint on the BBC One dance competition in late 2018.</p>

<p>She said: 'I'm good on my own, though. I'm pretty independent. </p>

<p>'It's nice to have that connection with someone, but at the moment lockdown is still [effectively] here, so "me" is where it is.'</p>

<p>She said about dating in lockdown: 'You can get to know someone a bit more before other "things" can happen… perhaps that's something that's positive. We'll see.'</p>

<p>Back to work: Ashley returned to her broadcasting duties last week after a sun-soaked summer holiday to Turkey </p>
